# The Ca2+ -mobilizing G protein (Gq) pathway; Modifying G protein Pathways (20)  

**Gq, Gs, and Gt protein effectors include some enzymes**  
  
**Genomic diversity of the G protein pathway**  
* ~ 1000 G protein-coupled receptors. All have 7 helices  
* G proteins all have 3 subunits  
* There are ~ 18 alpha subunit genes in 4 major classes i, q, s, t  
: ~ 5 beta subunits  
: ~ 3 gamma subunits 

**There are 2 major types of effectors**
(1) Channels affected by G proteins  
: ~5 known K+ channel genes  
: ~4 Ca2+ channels  
(2) Enzymes  
: 3 major classes, each with 2 to 10 members  
* and many “accessory proteins”. Now we discuss one  
  
**Regulators of G protein Signaling tune the kinetics of effector activation/deactivation**  
* Expressed: muscarinic acetylcholine receptor + G Protein-gated K+ channel.  
* + RGS protein  

**β-arrestins provide another example of tuning the G protein pathway** 
  
